   Here is the 50-49 roll call by which the
Senate defeated an amendment to the Clean Air bill Thursday that
would have provided special financial assistance to coal miners
hurt by new anti-pollution standards.
   On this question, a ``yes'' vote was a vote in favor of the
amendment and a ``no'' vote was a vote against the amendment.
   Voting ``yes'' were 38 Democrats and 11 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 16 Democrats and 34 Republicans.
   Senators not voting are denoted xxx.
